## Limitations

- File and folder layout is heuristic when PDB/DWARF is unavailable
- File hints come from strings, `__FILE__`, log tags, RTTI-like names, and callgraph clustering
- Variable names are IDA-generated in comments only; buildable stubs use stable synthetic symbols
- Struct layouts are opaque byte arrays sized from IDA metadata, not true field reconstructions
- Function logic is not preserved as compilable code; only a placeholder body is emitted
- Virtual function tables, exceptions, templates, and calling conventions are not reconstructed accurately

